NAIROBI &#8211; Burundi has informed UN Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon of its decision to quit the International Criminal Court (ICC), a Foreign Ministry official said on Wednesday.&#8220;An official document announcing Burundi&#8217;s move to quit the International Criminal Court was sent to Ban Ki-moon,&#8221; the permanent secretary at the ministry, Joseph Bangurambona, told Reuters.Another ministry source said the withdrawal document was dated October 19, a day after President Pierre Nkurunziza signed a decree to that effect.